8. Treat provenance limits plainly: the graph is strong on subsidy masquerading as yield, concentration, and contagion; it is not fraud detection.

The standard is portfolio-grade only if the base graph stays descriptive and the dependency/materiality/opacity judgments live in a separate versioned analytics layer. That is what keeps the object governable without pretending the scoring is objective.

